  '67bc56aa-639d-44ff-a923-17e2241b8cd8', 2023, '8.1', '2023-8.1', 'Insects as a food source for the future to feed the growing population',
  'Group Interaction', 'A webpage',
  '["Will everyone be eating insects by 2050?\nBy 2050 the population is expected to reach 9billion. To feed all of those hungry mouths, we will need to produce almost twice as much food as we currently do. But that isn''t going to be easy. One possible solution? Insects.\nEating insects is a common practice that''s been taking place for thousands of years. Around 2 billion people regularly eat insects as part of their diet, and over 1,900 species are edible. The most commonly eaten bugs are beetles, caterpillars, bees, wasps and ants.\nSo what''s so good about insects? Well, they''re nutritious and healthy. Insects actually have a high fat, protein, vitamin, fibre and mineral content that is often comparable to fish or livestock. Beetles, for example, contain on average 205 g/kg protein; beef contains 256 g/kg.\nRaising insects as a source of food as opposed to farmed animals is more environmentally friendly. Insects require significantly less land and water than traditionally-farmed animals and also reproduce much more quickly. Additionally, insects produce a fraction of the greenhouse gases when compared with other livestock, particularly cattle. Finally, insect farming can provide jobs and income to people living in poor areas. Insects are sustainable, green, nutritious and could help people out of poverty. Chocolate-covered caterpillars, anyone?"]'::jsonb,
  '["how eating insects can benefit people and the environment", "why people may not want to eat insects", "how to promote insects as food", "anything else you think is important"]'::jsonb,
  '[{"text": "Would you like to try eating insects?", "number": 1, "difficulty": "medium", "difficulty_level": "4-6"}, {"text": "Is eating healthy food important to people in Hong Kong?", "number": 2, "difficulty": "medium", "difficulty_level": "4-6"}, {"text": "Should people change their diet to help the environment?", "number": 3, "difficulty": "medium", "difficulty_level": "4-6"}, {"text": "Do you think Hong Kong should promote eating insects?", "number": 4, "difficulty": "medium", "difficulty_level": "4-6"}, {"text": "Should restaurants have insects on their menu?", "number": 5, "difficulty": "medium", "difficulty_level": "4-6"}, {"text": "Do you think Hongkongers will eat more healthy foods in the future?", "number": 6, "difficulty": "medium", "difficulty_level": "4-6"}, {"text": "Should Hong Kong develop insect farms?", "number": 7, "difficulty": "medium", "difficulty_level": "4-6"}, {"text": "Can people impact the environment by changing their diet?", "number": 8, "difficulty": "medium", "difficulty_level": "4-6"}]'::jsonb,
  '2026-02-11T16:18:37.673069+00:00', '2026-02-11T16:18:37.673069+00:00'
);
